Cauchari (Flagship Asset)
 Jujuy Province

Drilling planned April 2017. Permits in place allowing for up to 12 diamond drill and 5 rotary holes.
Key exploration target defined with a range of 0.25 to 5.6 mt of LCE and 0.9 mt to 16 mt of potash.
Potential to add significant brine volume at depth and laterally.
Cauchari brines similar to Olaroz (currently in production) in all important aspects, including a low magnesium to lithium ratio.
Exploration target based around total surface area of 55.44 km2 compared to the resource of 31km2

View Project  
      View Technical Report


Antofalla
 Salta & Catamarca Provinces

10,653 ha in the prospective Antofalla salar in the Salta and Catamarca Provinces
Pit samples returning results of 250 ppm lithium & 2,500 ppm potassium
Albermarle stated in their news release of Sept 12, 2016, that they believe their recent acquisition in Antofalla will host one of the largest lithium resources in Argentina

View Project


Incahuasi
 Salta Province, Argentina

Located in Salta province
Property Area: 9,843 ha
Pit sampling returning results up to 326 ppm lithium & 13,200 ppm potassium
Highest potassium values among the Argentine salars
Salta province of Argentina is ranked by Fraser Institute (2015 survey) as one of the most favourable jurisdictions in Central and South America for exploration

View Project


Guyatayoc
  Jujuy Province, Argentina

Located in Jujy province, 30 km north of Salinas Grandes salar
Property Area: 21,276 ha
Pit sampling returning results up to 200 ppm lithium & 7,000 ppm potassium
Low Magnesium/Lithium ratio

Learn More


Salinas Grande Salar
 Salta Province, Argentina
0.5% Royalty on 79,031 hectare Land Package in Salinas Grandes Salar*
*post Stella Marys transaction with LSC Lithium Corp


Clayton NE
 Clayton Valley Basin

2016/17 drill program has intersected lithium brines on all completed holes
5.4km mineralized brine trend
Located in the Clayton Valley Basin, Nevada
Contiguous to the eastern boundary of Albermarle’s Silver Peak Mines
Several lithium brine production wells are within approximately 110m west of the Clayton NE boundary

View Project


Jackson Wash
 Lida Valley Basin

Drill-ready with potential to host reservoir of lithium brine within an outlined gravity low
3,320 acres located in Lida Valley Basin, 30km south-east of Clayton Valley basin
Highly prospective basin analogous in sedimentary formations and underlying structures to Clayton Valley basin. Historically underexplored with no known drill tests in Lida Valley Basin

View Project


Gemini
  Lida Valley Basin

1,472 ha project immediately adjacent to a large, shallow depth, inferred resource
Prior exploration work includes mapping, sampling, geochemistry, drilling with pump tests and preliminary engineering

View Project


Neptune
 Clayton Valley Basin

6,320 acres located in southwest Clayton Valley Basin
Ten holes permitted by BLN. Two holes completed (and a 3rd abandoned) in 2016
Biogeochemical sample results show anomalous values up to 35 ppm Li near drill hole locations 

View Project


Aquarius
 Clayton Valley Basin

1,660 acres located in central Clayton Valley Basin
TDEM geophysical survey indicates a conductive horizons (possible brine) at depths of 820 – 1500 ft

View Project
















