The Mexico JV projects are located in large, closed basins with salar targets and surface-level lithium in geological settings analogous to the Clayton Valley basin. Geothermal hotsprings have been observed at the La Union and Viesca salars.
The region is underexplored, yet historic work by the Mexican Geologic Survey conducted in 1982 included drill hole at La Union which returned a brine sample of 283 ppm lithium and subsurface highly saline aquifers were also described in the historic data. Surface sampling conducted by Radius Gold returned numerous anomalous lithium results including 189ppm lithium at La Viesca.
Key Properties: Salta Province, Argentina
 The Stella Marys project covers 1,472 hectares in the western sector of the Salinas Grandes salar located in the province of Salta, Argentina. The Salinas Grandes salar is within the Lithium Triangle which hosts several early-stage, developing and producing lithium projects.
The Stella Marys project is adjacent to Orocobre’s Salar de Salinas Grandes project, which hosts a near-surface, low sulfate inferred resource estimate of 56.5 million cubic meters of brine grading 795 mg/l lithium (239,200 tonnes lithium carbonate equivalent) and 9,547 mg/l potassium (1.03 million tonnes of potash equivalent) and 283 mg/l boron.
Advantage Lithium Corp. (TSXV:AAL; OTCQX:AVLIF) has agreed to assign its option over the 1,471-hectare Stella Marys project, located in the Salinas Grandes salar in Salta province, Argentina, to LSC Lithium Corp. Advantage currently holds the MSR option pursuant to an agreement with Minera Santa Rita SRL dated Oct. 27, 2016.
Advantage will receive a 0.5% royalty on the brine concentrate produced from Salinas Grandes Tenements, calculated using the same methodology applied by Orocobre and its affiliates for the calculation of the royalties paid by Orocobre or its affiliates to the provincial government of Jujuy for Orocobre’s last two fiscal years (the “Salinas Grandes Royalty”) regardless of any retroactive or future changes to such methodology made after December 31, 2016.
David Sidoo, president and chief executive officer of Advantage Lithium, commented: “Stella Marys is a prospective project in a strategic location. This transaction allows us to monetize this asset, including a 0.5% royalty across the entire play pf 79,031 hectares, as LSC develops this considerable land package. The timing of the transaction is particularly beneficial as we prepare, with our partner, Orocobre, for an aggressive drill program at our advanced Cauchari project.”
“Acquiring a lithium brine project of this calibre in Argentina’s Lithium Triangle is a tremendous step forward for the company and our progress points clearly to calibre of the management and technical team we have assembled,” stated Sidoo.
Previous work at Stella Marys included a comprehensive exploration program of mapping and sampling, geochemistry, drilling with pump tests, and preliminary engineering.
Management
David Sidoo—President, CEO and Director
David Sidoo has a strong track record of taking companies from start-up to successful sale while delivering substantial shareholder value. He is an award-winning senior executive (Order of BC, Vancouver Sun’s “Top 100 South Asians making a Difference in BC) as well as founder and significant shareholder of American Oil & Gas (sold to Hess in all stock transition valued at $630M+). Sidoo sits on the Board of Governors for University of British Columbia.
Dev Randhawa—Director
Dev Randhawa is the founding CEO and Chairman of Fission Uranium and has been instrumental in leading the company to Tier 1 status. He was also Founder of Pacific Asia China Energy which sold for $34 million. Randhawa was named Finance Monthly “Dealmaker of the Year” and Northern Miner “Mining Person of the Year”.
Ross McElroy, P. Geol.—Director and Technical Advisor
Ross McElroy is a professional geologist with nearly 30 years of experience in mining industry. He is also the also the President, COO and Chief Geologist for Fission Uranium and has lead the team to success with 2 major discoveries in 3 years. McElroy was the DAC 2014 Bill Dennis Award winner and has also won Northern Miner’s “Mining Person of the Year”.
Doug Leishman, BSc. ARSM—Chairman of the Advisory Board
Doug Leishman is a highly experienced geologist and mining analyst with more than 30 years in the mining industry. He is a director of several successful resource companies, including Fortress Minerals Corp., a Lundin Group company, and Terrane Metals Corp.
Simon Ridgway—Advisory Board Member
Simon Ridgway is a prospector, a mining financier and a Casey Research Explorer’s League inductee. Grass roots exploration has provided him with a successful career as a prospector since starting out in the Yukon Territory in the late 70s. Ridgway and the exploration teams under his guidance have discovered gold deposits in Honduras, Guatemala, Nicaragua and continue that success globally. Companies operating under the Gold Group banner have raised over $400 million for exploration and development projects since 2003. He is a founder and Chairman of Fortuna Silver Mines, and founder and CEO of Radius Gold, Medgold Resources and Focus Ventures.
 
